go to the Intel site, download 30056401.PDF Title is Intel Pentium 4 on 90 nm Process thermal design guide.
On page 26 it shows how the PROCOHT# signal modulates the Normal clock by an internal clock duty cycle resulting in an intermittent clock rate that allows the CPU to keep running at a slower rate, thus reducing the power consumption.
Further on one can read about the shutdown signal.
